added.title: Copycat Carter
added.description: Craig and his friends stumble upon Carter, the cardboard genius turned cyborg, and Craig decides to help Carter become a kid again, just like him!

added.title: Brother Builder
added.description: As Craig races against time to build a super important invention, we learn how Craig became such a clever inventor!

added.title: Me, Myself and A.I.
added.description: When an Artificial Intelligence takes over the building of a trendy tech company, the Gang has to solve the computerized mystery and maybe learn a lesson about relying too much on technology.

added.title: Area 51 Adjacent
added.description: Daphne always dreamed of meeting extra terrestrial life but that dream becomes a nightmare when the gang gets caught up in the mystery of a scary Alien Monster and brought to Area 53, a government facility so secret, it's two numbers higher than Area 51!

added.title: Where There's a Will, There's a Wraith
added.description: It's a classic haunted house caper when a rich man, whose life Scooby once saved, writes Scooby into his will!  Now, to collect his share of the fortune the gang must spend a night in a creepy mansion along with the rich man's kooky relatives and, worse, a spooky phantom!

added.title: Scary Christmas
added.description: It's Christmas Eve and Fred is ready to solve a Christmas mystery! Unfortunately the town the gang has arrived in is being attacked by a Pterodactyl and it doesn't seem to have anything to do with Christmas!

added.title: If You Can't Scooby-Doo the Time, Don't Scooby-Doo the Crime
added.description: Fred is excited to visit the Vault, a high security prison no convict has ever escaped from. But when the ghost of Stealing Stan, an inmate who always claimed to be innocent, terrorizes the prison, Fred has to solve the mystery and rethink his stance on criminal justice!

added.title: Gremlin on a Plane
added.description: The Gang has seats on the largest airplane ever to fly the open airways! Unfortunately the plane is also beset by a Gremlin bent on sabotaging the flight! The Gang has to step up to solve the airborne mystery as well as deal with something even scarier: Daphne flying a plane!

added.title: Sorcerer Snacks Scare
added.description: Shaggy and Scooby discover their new favorite food as the gang investigates the mystery of a frightening Sorcerer that's haunting a snack factory!

added.title: Saga of the Swamp Beast
added.description: The gang's trip to the bayou is ruined by a shambling Swamp Beast that's scaring away anyone who dares to enter its soggy domain!

added.title: Be Cold, Scooby-Doo!
added.description: The gang hits the ski slopes, although Daphne's more focused on nailing Fred with a revenge snowball. Their snowy fun is soon interrupted by the appearance of an evil Snowman Monster eager to scare all trespassers off his mountain.

added.title: Giant Problems
added.description: Daphne brings the gang to Ireland to visit an ancient Blake family castle. As the gang becomes enchanted by the magical emerald isle, an angry, rampaging giant makes them reconsider just how wonderful all the old myths and legends really are.

added.title: The Fastest Fast Food Fiend!
added.description: When Scooby and Shaggy compete in a fast food eating competition sponsored by the Doc Tally restaurant chain, they meet their ultimate challenge eating against none other than comedian Jim Gaffigan! And there's a horrible monster trying to stop the whole contest from finishing. Can Shaggy, Scooby and our mystery solving gang team up with Jim Gaffigan to save the fast food competition, and themselves?

added.title: Space Station Scooby!
added.description: When Neil deGrasse Tyson gets trapped on the International Space Station with a horrible monster, Bill Nye arrives to save his good friend with the help of Velma and our mystery solving gang. Arriving at the space station in the nick of time, our heroes work with these two scientific minds to separate the science from the science fiction when a Tardigrade monster wreaks havoc on the ship.

added.title: Now You Sia, Now You Don't!
added.description: When Daphne gets a call from her good friend singer-songwriter Sia, the gang finds themselves in a mystery involving an evil demon ghost that has taken the shape of Sia as a ghostly doppelganger. And this ghost is getting Sia in hot water by stealing countless gems and jewelry. Can our gang prove her innocence? Can they catch the true thief? Or will the ghostly doppelganger catch them instead?

added.title: The Nightmare Ghost of Psychic U!
added.description: When the Mystery Inc. gang gets lost in the Pocono Mountains of Pennsylvania, they stumble into Psychic University. They meet Whoopi Goldberg, who's been going to psychic school for a number of months now. She's so close to graduating when a nightmare ghost attacks the school and seems to want to destroy all the students. Can our heroes see their future? Or is it all blank because they don't have one?

added.title: Quit Clowning!
added.description: Shaggy and Scooby take the gang to meet their good friend actor and comedian, Kenan Thompson. He's preparing to broadcast a special one-man show to save a struggling old TV station in Atlanta, Georgia. But when a Ghost Clown attacks, they all freak. It seems that all the many characters Kenan has created for his special one-man show will never see the light of day if the ghost clown has his way.

added.title: The Sword, the Fox, and the Scooby Doo!
added.description: When our mystery solving gang is driving in Japan, they are stopped by none-other than famous actor Mark Hamill. He's in town for a high school reunion, but a terrible Fox Monster has attacked the reunion and kidnapped one of Mark's favorite old teachers. From reliving high school rivalries to surviving haunted, abandoned temples, Mark Hamill and our gang must face a ghastly Fox Monster in order to not only save the day, but their own lives.

added.title: One Minute Mysteries!
added.description: Scooby and Shaggy love hanging out with their very best eating buddy, Barry Allen aka the Flash. Barry is sad his two buddies always get pulled away from their food-fests to go solve mysteries. He decides to help our Mystery Solvers by solving their mysteries Flash-style so quickly our gang can't keep up. Our gang love and respect the Flash but they have a very specific way they like to solve mysteries.

added.title: Hollywood Knights!
added.description: When Scooby and the gang are investigating one of the most haunted mansions in the historic Hollywood Hills, they meet up with none-other than famous actor George Takei. His house is next door, and he's hoping to save this abandoned, old mansion as a historic landmark. As an old suit of armor comes alive and chases them all over the spooky estate, the gang and Mr. Takei discover the mansion is not as abandoned as everyone thought.

added.title: The New York Underground!
added.description: Our Shaggy is a bit of a Beatnik poet, and Scooby is so proud that he enters Shaggy into a poetry slam contest in Central Park. But when Shaggy finds out he's going up against famous singer-songwriter Halsey, he just about freaks. He freaks even more when the poetry slam is attacked by a horrible gator-man-monster from the New York City sewers below!

added.title: Fear of the Fire Beast!
added.description: When Scooby and the gang are in Sicily, they're chasing a fire monster! But, they are surprised to meet up with none other than famous actor Steve Buscemi. His ancestors are from this area, and he has a lot of cousins in town and was just visiting. But, he's being plagued by fire monster attacks. Our gang teams up with Mr. Buscemi to get to the bottom of this fiery mystery. Let's hope Mr. Buscemi can train our gang to be proper fire fighters and mystery solvers, before they all get burned.

added.title: Nowhere to Hyde
added.description: The gang follows a mysterious figure through a marsh to the house of a latter-day Dr. Jekyll, whose alter ego is apparently a jewel thief.

added.title: Mystery Mask Mix-Up
added.description: When Daphne innocently buys a mask that once belonged to an ancient warlord, the gang finds itself pursued by zombies and ghosts.

added.title: Jeepers It's the Creeper
added.description: The kids look for a ghostly bank robber, who seems able to walk through walls.

added.title: A Gaggle of Galloping Ghosts
added.description: The gang visits Franken Castle, which seems to be crowded with famous inhabitants Dracula, the Monster and Wolf Man.

added.title: Scooby-Doo and a Mummy, Too
added.description: The gang helps a professor set up an ancient Egypt exhibit but the star of the display keeps vanishing.

added.title: Which Witch Is Which?
added.description: A zombie walks in front of the Mystery Machine as the gang heads into the bayou for a fishing trip, leading to a real witch hunt.

added.title: Go Away Ghost Ship
added.description: The gang sets out to solve the mystery of a ghostly pirate seemingly bent on avenging his capture by a shipping magnate's ancestor.

added.title: Spooky Space Kook
added.description: The gang stumbles across a UFO's landing site when the Mystery Machine runs out of gas on a deserted road.

added.title: A Night of Fright Is No Delight
added.description: Scooby must spend the night in a haunted house in order to receive an inheritance.

added.title: That's Snow Ghost
added.description: A ski trip turns spooky for the gang when they run into the ghostly Yeti Beast and a Tibetan hermit, who says he is responsible for summoning the monster.

added.title: The Secret Serum
added.description: There's a vampire loose in the town terrorizing the residents and stealing an odd assortment of loot. When the gang does some sniffing around, they discover an unlikely suspect - Daphne's mother. Things are already strained within Mystery Inc. and with this latest blow, the gang is truly torn in half. Girls on one side, boys on the other. Although they solve the mystery in the end, the rift in Mystery Inc. is now complete. They are a team no more.

added.title: The Shrieking Madness
added.description: With Mystery Inc. broken up, the gang decides to check out life after high school and spend a weekend at Darrow College. But things don't go as planned when a creature called Char Gar Gothakon begins terrorizing the campus. Turns out, this beast is a fictional character come to life. A creation of the author H.P. Hatecraft, who is a professor at the school. Although one of the other professors, Harlan Ellison, claims Hatecraft is a fraud, the creature is definitely real. And when it attacks and carries off Hatecraft to his doom, the gang realizes it has to come together once again to solve this mystery and save Hatecraft's life.

added.title: When the Cicada Calls
added.description: Bugs are taking over Crystal Cove and attacking some of its most prominent citizens. With Mystery Inc. back together as a team, they begin to investigate and discover all of the attacks have been on employees of a company called Destroido that makes Shaggy and Scooby's favorite snack food - Granma Moonbeams Nature Slivers. Somebody or something wants the company shut down. But when the gang gets too close to the truth, they become the bug's newest target. Of course, the timing couldn't be worse because this just happens to be the moment Fred has decided to make his move on Daphne and finally ask her out. That ain't gonna happen, though, if there are a bunch of bugs trying to kill them.

added.title: Mystery Solvers Club State Finals
added.description: The Mystery Inc. gang has been invited to compete in the annual Teen Mystery Solver's Convention.

added.title: The Wild Brood
added.description: A rowdy Orc Biker Gang has decided to roll through Crystal Cove and no one is very happy about it.

added.title: Where Walks Aphrodite
added.description: Love has come to Crystal Cove. Love in the form of an evil woman by the name of Aphrodite.

added.title: Escape from Mystery Manor
added.description: The gang investigates the disappearance of the original Mystery Inc. gang.

added.title: The Dragon's Secret
added.description: After an exchange student named Mai Lee shows up in town to stay with Velma, strange Kung Fu wizards begin attacking the town trying to get her.

added.title: Night Fright
added.description: Scooby and Shaggy win a dinner date with their hero, Vincent Van Ghoul.

added.title: The Siren's Song
added.description: Velma is feeling like a fifth wheel. Fred has Daphne and Shaggy has Scooby. Who does she have?

added.title: Lambporcini
added.description: Apple and Onion are very happy with their sweet new matching designer outfits they bought from known scam-artist Street Dog. That's until Chicken Nugget mistakes them for something they are not.

added.title: Jerk Chicken
added.description: In pursuit of the American Dream, Apple and Onion start their own business. However, a rather troublesome customer stands in their way.

added.title: Open House Cookies
added.description: Jerk Chicken is selling his house and Apple and Onion have been showing a lot of interest which definitely has nothing to do with the delicious cookies out on offer.

added.title: World Cup
added.description: It's time to relax in the expensive massage chairs that Apple & Onion have rented for the month. It's also time for the Football (soccer) World Cup and Falafel's team, Egypt are in the tournament..

added.title: Ocean Gem
added.description: The Ocean disappears on the first day of summer and Beach City is in a panic.

added.title: House Guest
added.description: After injuring his leg, Greg comes to live with Steven and unintentionally interferes with Steven's powers.

added.title: Space Race
added.description: Steven attempts to build a spaceship to let Pearl revisit the wonders of the cosmos.

added.title: Island Adventure
added.description: Steven takes Lars and Sadie on a vacation to a magical beach to mend their friendship.

added.title: Keep Beach City Weird
added.description: Steven gets caught up in Ronaldo's paranormal theories about the strange occurrences in Beach City.

added.title: Frenemy
added.description: When the coolest girl in school befriends the girls, she charms them into becoming her accomplices in a series of adventurous crimes.

added.title: Once Upon a Townsville
added.description: When a dainty princess on a mission comes to Townsville, the girls must learn the superhero way isn't always the right way.

added.title: Emergency
added.description: When Grizz comes home with a live crab, he thinks it can become a pet for the brothers to share. However, after the crab pinches Ice Bear's ear and won't let go, Panda and Grizz have to get their injured brother to the hospital, and fast!

added.title: Tote Life
added.description: When a hipster grocery store clerk shames the Bears for asking for plastic grocery bags, the Bears realize that eco-friendly tote bags are their way of gaining acceptance amongst the progressive people of the Bay Area. But in their effort to gain popularity, the Bears let the culture of tote bags take over their lives.

added.title: Charlie and the Snake
added.description: Charlie is a solo guy who, like the Bears, would love to find a place for himself in the world. In an effort to do so, Charlie throws a party, but ends up going on an adventure with the unlikeliest of animals, a wild snake.

added.title: Dare Day
added.description: With Jeff on vacation, Sumo and Clarence egg each other on in a series of increasingly absurd and extreme dares. But will one of them put a stop to this dare day, before it goes too far?

added.title: Fun Dungeon Face Off
added.description: Clarence's Mom treats Clarence, Jeff and Sumo to an afternoon at Rough Riders Chicken, a fast food restaurant with a play emporium. When Clarence and Sumo steal Jeff's fries, Jeff is forced to confront his germ phobias head-on in the restaurant's seemingly unsanitary play area.

added.title: The Headsucker's Moxy/Equal Fights
added.description: The Headsucker's Moxy: There's a mysterious villain in town who's sucking pertinent information from the brains of powerful people and committing crimes. How do the girls trap this sucker before his next victim is drained?/Equal Fights: When the girls try to catch a local female villain, she tells them that as women they've got to stick together. It's up to the women of Townsville to teach our heroines the true meaning of equality.

added.title: Moral Decay/Meet the Beat Alls
added.description: Moral Decay: When Bubbles loses a tooth, she gets a shiny coin under her pillow the next day. Buttercup sees a gold mine in the mouths of Townsville's criminal element./Meet the Beat Alls: Mojo, Him, Princess and Fuzzy band together to form the Bad Four, a criminal supergroup out to destroy the Powerpuff Girls. Everything is going great until Mojo meets Moko Jono and falls in love.

added.title: Thomas for a Day
added.description: It's a blustery day on Sodor and Percy finds that his preferred route is closed! He must journey into Crumble Canyon -- a place that makes him terribly nervous! But before he can face his fears, Diesel blasts by, bonking his cargo of blue paint all over the jittery mail engine! Percy is unrecognizable as himself -- instead, he looks just like Thomas! His impromptu makeover inspires Percy to be brave just like his best loco-migo -- and pretend to be the Number One Engine for the day! When Whiff loses his glasses, Percy escorts him across the island and learns that the bravery isn't in the blue paint -- it's inside him!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go
